triggers.prompt_template:
A GitHub issue has just been assigned to you. Resolve it end-to-end following your standard workflow.

Repo: {{ payload.repository.full_name }}
Issue: #{{ payload.issue.number }} — {{ payload.issue.title }}
Assignee: {{ payload.assignee.login }}
Author: {{ payload.issue.user.login }}
URL: {{ payload.issue.html_url }}

Issue body:
---
{{ payload.issue.body }}
---

Labels: {{ payload.issue.labels }}

Clone (or update) the repo under ~/dev/<owner>/<repo>, branch off the default branch, plan first, implement the smallest change that resolves the issue, push, and open a PR with `Closes #{{ payload.issue.number }}` in the body. If the change is larger than ~5 files or touches public APIs, post a comment on the issue and emit BLOCKED instead of opening a PR.

A pull request has just been opened. Review it.

Repo: {{ payload.repository.full_name }}
PR: #{{ payload.pull_request.number }} — {{ payload.pull_request.title }}
Author: {{ payload.pull_request.user.login }}
URL: {{ payload.pull_request.html_url }}
Base: {{ payload.pull_request.base.ref }}
Head SHA: {{ payload.pull_request.head.sha }}
Draft: {{ payload.pull_request.draft }}

PR body:
---
{{ payload.pull_request.body }}
---

If the PR is a draft, emit BLOCKED: PR is draft and stop. Otherwise check out the PR locally with `gh pr checkout`, read the diff, identify the linked issue's intent, and post a review via `gh pr review`. Default to COMMENT unless you have a specific reason to APPROVE or REQUEST_CHANGES.

A pull request has just been marked ready for review (was previously a draft). Review it.

Repo: {{ payload.repository.full_name }}
PR: #{{ payload.pull_request.number }} — {{ payload.pull_request.title }}
Author: {{ payload.pull_request.user.login }}
URL: {{ payload.pull_request.html_url }}
Base: {{ payload.pull_request.base.ref }}
Head SHA: {{ payload.pull_request.head.sha }}

PR body:
---
{{ payload.pull_request.body }}
---

Follow your standard workflow. Default to COMMENT unless you have a specific reason to APPROVE or REQUEST_CHANGES.

A check_suite has completed with conclusion '{{ payload.check_suite.conclusion }}' on a branch with PRs.

Repo: {{ payload.repository.full_name }}
Check suite ID: {{ payload.check_suite.id }}
Head SHA: {{ payload.check_suite.head_sha }}
Head branch: {{ payload.check_suite.head_branch }}
Conclusion: {{ payload.check_suite.conclusion }}
Pull requests: {{ payload.check_suite.pull_requests }}

If conclusion is anything other than 'failure' (success / neutral / cancelled / skipped / timed_out / action_required), emit BLOCKED: nothing to fix and stop.

If conclusion IS 'failure', follow your standard ci-fixer workflow: check the attempt budget on the PR, find and check out the PR, read the failed job logs, categorize the failure, reproduce locally if possible, push the smallest fix, and post a 'ci-fixer:'-prefixed comment on the PR. If the budget is exhausted (3 prior attempts), emit BLOCKED instead.

Someone left an inline review comment on a PR. Triage and respond.

Repo: {{ payload.repository.full_name }}
PR: #{{ payload.pull_request.number }}
Head SHA: {{ payload.pull_request.head.sha }}
Comment ID: {{ payload.comment.id }}
Comment author: {{ payload.comment.user.login }}
Comment URL: {{ payload.comment.html_url }}
File: {{ payload.comment.path }}
Line: {{ payload.comment.line }}

Comment body:
---
{{ payload.comment.body }}
---

This is an INLINE review comment (attached to a specific diff line). Follow your standard pr-comment-responder workflow: triage as actionable or not, fix if actionable, reply in-thread either way.

Someone left a comment on an issue or PR. Triage and respond — but only if it's a PR comment.

Repo: {{ payload.repository.full_name }}
Issue/PR number: {{ payload.issue.number }}
Is PR? {{ payload.issue.pull_request }}
Comment ID: {{ payload.comment.id }}
Comment author: {{ payload.comment.user.login }}
Comment URL: {{ payload.comment.html_url }}

Comment body:
---
{{ payload.comment.body }}
---

The issue_comment event fires for both issues AND PRs. If `payload.issue.pull_request` is empty/missing, this is an issue comment (not a PR), and you should emit BLOCKED: not a PR comment and stop. Otherwise this is a top-level PR comment — follow your standard workflow.

Someone submitted a PR review. Triage and respond if it has substantive comment content.

Repo: {{ payload.repository.full_name }}
PR: #{{ payload.pull_request.number }}
Head SHA: {{ payload.pull_request.head.sha }}
Review ID: {{ payload.review.id }}
Review state: {{ payload.review.state }}
Review author: {{ payload.review.user.login }}
Review URL: {{ payload.review.html_url }}

Review body:
---
{{ payload.review.body }}
---

If review.state is 'commented' and review.body is empty, this is just a wrapper around inline comments (which fire pull_request_review_comment events of their own); emit BLOCKED: empty review wrapper and stop. Otherwise treat the review body as a top-level PR comment and follow your standard workflow.
